      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the immediate prevention of massacres was a tactical success, the geopolitical failure of the intervention is undeniable because it failed to achieve its *ultimate* goal of establishing a stable, democratic Libya. Any military action that precipitates a decade of civil war and regional instability cannot be deemed a success, regardless of its initial humanitarian victories. The intervention merely replaced one authoritarian problem with a far more dangerous, protracted state failure.",
